  "body_html": "<p>Physics departments are at risk of shutting down across the world. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png\" width=\"1247\" height=\"619\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:619,&quot;width&quot;:1247,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:92017,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/i/174224913?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gAjY!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F54e5ec83-4444-43e4-b656-df8cdfed18ba_1247x619.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>I have restrained myself from being political on this blog. That being said, one obvious response is to campaign for more money. We can mail politicians to increase funding for physics. We can also ask for money from philanthropists. All are good things to do. </p><p>But let\u2019s <em>assume</em> that these cuts are here to stay, and that funding won\u2019t budge. I am worried that this is a possibility too. </p><p>In this case, independent scientists who work alongside a day job could be an imperfect, but valuable solution. </p><p>The scientific method doesn\u2019t belong to organisations, and anyone can be empirical.  Most of the science before the 1900s was done independently anyways. In that spirit, I am trying to do math, trying to do experiments at home, and publishing those ideas on this blog. I wish that ex-physicists more talented than me would get in the game as well, because I still suck at it! </p><p><a href=\"https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/p/i-want-to-do-experiments-but-its\">Experiments are hard because they\u2019re expensive</a>, but trying to make them cheaper and recording the attempt is still progress. It\u2019s also possible to work on theory by contributing to open source projects like <a href=\"https://physlean.com/\">PhysLean</a>. </p><p>Having people doing physics in their garages is an imperfect solution, but I think it\u2019s net positive versus people doing nothing. There\u2019s a risk that campaigning will lead nowhere, and so citizen science feels like a great hedge for society. </p><p>I am disappointed that I had to write this post. But on the bright side, it\u2019s an environment where independent researchers can have their day in the sun, because we are used to having little resources anyway. </p><p>It\u2019s worth noting however, that there is a risk that governments could use this as an excuse to cut funding more and over-rely on independents (or corporations). I think this risk is small for now, but could get bigger. <strong>This is why not having budget cuts would be the best solution.</strong> </p><div><hr></div><h3>Acknowledgements </h3><p>Thank you to Cyrus Hafezparast for bringing this to my attention </p>",
